Given the following text, do the benefits of smoking cigarettes outweigh the risks? Explain how you came to your conclusion.

Text: Smoking cigarettes is said to help significantly reduce stress, help people relax, concentrate, and boost mental strength. Smoking can also be a good way to control hypertension in some circumstances. Smoking cigarettes is also a good way to reduce the possibility of becoming obese and can be an icebreaker in social situations. Conversely, smoking has been proven to causes cancer, heart disease, stroke, lung diseases, diabetes, and chronic obstructive pulmonary disease (COPD), which includes emphysema and chronic bronchitis. Smoking also increases risk for tuberculosis, certain eye diseases, and problems of the immune system, including rheumatoid arthritis.